---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="GovCon Velocity — You're on the Waitlist">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-20 text-center">
    <div class="w-20 h-20 bg-[rgba(229,183,60,0.15)] rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6">
      <span class="text-4xl">🎉</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="font-['Manrope'] text-4xl font-bold text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">You're on the Waitlist</h1>
    <p class="text-[#666] text-lg mb-8 max-w-md mx-auto leading-relaxed">
      Thanks for your interest in GovCon Velocity. We'll email you the moment subscriptions open — no spam, no sales calls.
    </p>
    <div class="bg-white border border-[#DED8D0] rounded-xl p-8 max-w-sm mx-auto mb-8">
      <p class="text-sm text-[#666] mb-2">What happens next:</p>
      <ul class="text-sm text-[#333] space-y-2 text-left">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#E5B73C] shrink-0">1.</span> We're building the data pipeline right now</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#E5B73C] shrink-0">2.</span> You'll receive a single email when subscriptions open</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#E5B73C] shrink-0">3.</span> Early-access pricing available for waitlist members</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-[#999] mb-8">In the meantime, check the ATOM retirement deadline. It's July 31 — don't get caught without a feed.</p>
    <a href="/data/govcon-intel" class="inline-block bg-[#E5B73C] text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-md font-['Manrope'] font-bold hover:bg-[#CDA333] transition-colors">
      Back to GovCon Velocity
    </a>
  </section>
</Layout>